## Status Color System

Eight color families for consistent status representation across the app.

| Family | CSS Variable Prefix | Hue | Use Cases |
|--------|-------------------|-----|-----------|
| Emerald (Success) | `--status-success` | 142 | Completed, active, delivered, paid |
| Amber (Warning) | `--status-warning` | 38 | Pending review, expiring soon, at risk |
| Red (Danger) | `--status-danger` | 0 | Failed, rejected, overdue, cancelled |
| Blue (Info) | `--status-info` | 217 | New, informational, default state |
| Gray (Neutral) | `--status-neutral` | 220 | Draft, inactive, archived, N/A |
| Indigo (In Progress) | `--status-in-progress` | 239 | In transit, processing, in review |
| Violet (Queued) | `--status-queued` | 263 | Scheduled, queued, waiting |
| Cyan (Special) | `--status-special` | 186 | Highlighted, featured, priority |

### Status Token Structure (per family)
```css
--status-{family}-bg:       /* Badge/chip background (light) */
--status-{family}-text:     /* Badge/chip text color */
--status-{family}-border:   /* Badge/chip border */
--status-{family}-dot:      /* Dot indicator fill */
```

